  "text": "In contrast, the presence of chloride affects very little both the Tl(I) and Pb(II) signals, because the corresponding formation constants for their predominant complexes are much smaller (TlCl [aq] Log K = 0.51, [CITATION_1] ). If the sample does not contain chloride, it is preferable to use the acetate buffer to attain the Cu(II) peaks with no altered potential (0.00-0.05 V), minimizing its interfering potential with the Tl(I) determination.",
